# Distribusi *Sampling*

## CLT *(Central Limit Theorem)*

CENTRAL LIMIT THEOREM : Semakin besar sampel yang diambil, bisa didekatkan ke dist. normal

Sampling Distribution (Contoh: akan dilakukan sampling dari distribusi uniform)


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
unif <- c(1:8)
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
unif
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8
```


:::
:::


Lihat sebarannya


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mean(unif)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] 4.5
```


:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
sd(unif)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] 2.44949
```


:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hist(unif, main = "Uniform Distribution", xlab = " ")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](modul3_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-15-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


Ambil berbagai ukuran sampel, bandingkan


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
set.seed(211)
```
:::


